<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>A Person</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 1.95pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 324pt; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Supplementary written evidence submitted by the Rt Hon Gregory Barker MP, DECC (HOT0062)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I would like to thank you for inviting me to speak to the Energy &amp;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Climate Change Committee on Tuesday. I hope you found the information that my officials and I provided helpful. I recognise that on a number of occasions, we could not give you answers in full and undertook to write to you. Having gone through the officia</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">l record, I hope that the following further information fulfils that commitment. Please do let us know if there is any further information you require. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Regulations on Heating Controls</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Standard Assessment Procedure for demonstrating compliance with Bui</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">lding Regulations currently do effectively penalise the construction of a new home without appropriate heating controls – one part of the model adjusts the internal temperature and/or   assumed efficiency of the heating system in line with the effectivenes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s of the control system. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Similarly on the installation of a full new heating system in an existing dwelling there is a requirement under Part L of the Building Regulations that reasonable provision is made for the installation of effective controls includ</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ing timer, room thermostat and TRVs.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In our Energy Efficiency Strategy we announced a programme to assess the potential of smarter heating controls to reduce domestic energy demand. The evidence base is currently mixed on the issue of the extent to which s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">marter heating controls reduce energy consumption. It suggests further development is needed to meet user requirements of different groups. DECC have recently published new research to test the usability of five currently available Smarter Heating Controls</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. The findings, published in full on the gov.uk website, highlight the need for further innovation in heating control design and usability.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The next stage of the Smarter Heating Controls research programme will be to work closely with industry leads on how</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> new products can be improved and to develop further evidence on whether they reduce energy c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">onsumption.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Green Deal Application in Devolved Areas</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Green Deal offer is the same across the constituent nations of the UK. However, there were some difference</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s in delivery in Scotland:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In Scotland Green Deal launched on 28 January alongside the GB wide launch. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">IT systems became fully operational on 25 February to lodge Green Deal plans. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In addition to GB wide information</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the GB-wide Oversight and Registration Body has certified assessors registered on the Scottish EPC database </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">who </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">able to make and lodge assessments</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> more a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">re</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> registering</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Scotland has participated and part funded the Scotland-specific elements of the G</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">B wide marketing campaign, in addition to activity by the Scottish Government, including </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a variation on the Cashback offer, which did not at first include a Green Deal Assessment (it has since April 2013).</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Energy Saving Scotland Advice Centre remote ad</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">vice centres are reporting increased call levels around Green Deal.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">We collect statistics around the UK for Green Deal </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> ECO uptake, as set out below:</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><table cellspacin